        <para>
                When you access Tamboti, the search interface appears. On the interface:
            </para>
        <para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>Below the Tamboti logo, there are buttons for <guibutton>Login</guibutton> and <guibutton>Help</guibutton>.</listitem>
                <listitem>Below, there is a set of tabs. The tabs open by default on Simple Search: the other tabs are Advanced Search, Query
                        History and My List. The functions that these tabs give access to will be explained below; they are similar to functions found in most
                        library catalogues.</listitem>
                <listitem>Below the tab area, you find a grey vertical column, headed by the Folder View button.</listitem>
                <listitem>To the right of the Folder View button, you see the found count for the current search. There are also links for navigating to the next and previous groups of search hits, and to the first and last group.</listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
